---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  pageType="guide"
  guideTopic="permits"
  title="Do You Need a Permit for a Shipping Container? | Steel Box Direct"
  description="Permit and zoning requirements for shipping containers vary by location and use. Confirming them is the buyer's responsibility before purchasing."
  datePublished="2026-03-10"
  dateModified="2026-06-24"
>
  <div class="guide-header guide_header" style="background: var(--c5-permits); color: var(--cream);">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="sh guide_eyebrow" style="border-color: var(--cream);">
        <span class="idx">§ 05</span>
        <span class="nm" style="color: var(--cream);">Decision: Permits</span>
        <span class="tg" style="color: var(--cream);">Zoning & Land Use</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="big guide_headline" style="color: var(--cream);">Do I need<br><em>A permit?</em></h1>
      <p class="guide-lede guide_lede" style="opacity: .9;">
        It depends on where you are and how you'll use the container. Permit and zoning rules vary by county,
        municipality, and intended use — and it's the buyer's responsibility to confirm them with the local
        authority before purchasing. We do not determine, advise on, or guarantee permit requirements.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="guide-content guide_content">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="row guide_main_row">
        <div class="main-col guide_main_col">
          <h2>Requirements vary by location and use</h2>
          <p>Whether a permit is required depends on your jurisdiction and what you plan to do with the container. The factors below commonly affect requirements — they are general examples, not a determination for your property. Always confirm with your local zoning or building authority before you buy.</p>

          <div class="permit-card guide_comparison_item" style="border-left-color: var(--c4-cost);">
            <h3>Factors that commonly affect requirements</h3>
            <div class="m guide_comparison_item_meta" style="color: var(--c4-cost); margin-bottom: 12px;">General examples only</div>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Property classification:</strong> Agricultural, residential, or commercial zoning.</li>
              <li><strong>Incorporated vs. unincorporated:</strong> Properties inside city limits often face more rules.</li>
              <li><strong>Intended use:</strong> Plain storage versus conversion to office or living space.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="permit-card guide_comparison_item" style="border-left-color: var(--c2-cond);">
            <h3>Situations that more often require review</h3>
            <div class="m guide_comparison_item_meta" style="color: var(--c2-cond); margin-bottom: 12px;">Check before you buy</div>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Habitable space:</strong> Conversion to an office or living quarters.</li>
              <li><strong>Property lines:</strong> Placement near a boundary or required setback.</li>
              <li><strong>City limits / HOA:</strong> Incorporated areas and deed-restricted neighborhoods.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <aside class="sidebar-col guide_sidebar_col">
          <div class="authority-card guide_callout">
            <div class="m guide_callout_label">Your responsibility</div>
            <ul>
              <li>Confirm requirements with your <strong>county or municipal</strong> zoning/building department.</li>
              <li>Do this <strong>before you purchase</strong> — rules and enforcement vary widely.</li>
              <li>We do <strong>not</strong> determine, advise on, or guarantee permit outcomes.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="cta-card guide_cta">
            <h4 class="guide_cta_headline">Ready when you are</h4>
            <p>We're glad to help with size, condition, and delivery. Confirming permit and zoning requirements is up to you and your local authority.</p>
            <a href="/quote/" class="btn guide_cta_btn">Get a Quote <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 12h14M13 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg></a>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .guide-header {
      padding: 80px 0 64px;
      border-bottom: 2.5px solid var(--ink);
    }
    .guide-lede {
      font-size: 22px;
      line-height: 1.45;
      margin: 40px 0 0;
      max-width: 720px;
      font-weight: 500;
    }

    .guide-content {
      padding: 96px 0;
      background: var(--cream);
    }

    .row {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1.5fr 1fr;
      gap: 80px;
      align-items: start;
    }

    .permit-card {
      background: white;
      border: 2px solid var(--ink);
      border-left: 8px solid var(--ink);
      padding: 32px;
      margin-top: 40px;
      box-shadow: 8px 8px 0 var(--ink);
    }
    .permit-card h3 {
      font-family: var(--narrow);
      font-weight: 700;
      font-size: 28px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }
    .permit-card ul {
      margin: 20px 0 0;
      padding: 0;
      list-style: none;
    }
    .permit-card li {
      padding: 8px 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(11,15,26,.1);
      font-size: 15px;
      line-height: 1.45;
    }
    .permit-card li:last-child { border: none; }

    .authority-card {
      background: var(--ink);
      color: var(--cream);
      padding: 32px;
      border: 2px solid var(--ink);
    }
    .authority-card .m { color: var(--yellow); margin-bottom: 16px; }
    .authority-card ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
    .authority-card li { margin-bottom: 16px; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.45; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(246,241,231,.1); padding-bottom: 16px; }
    .authority-card li:last-child { border: none; }

    .cta-card {
      margin-top: 40px;
      background: white;
      border: 2px solid var(--ink);
      padding: 32px;
      box-shadow: 8px 8px 0 var(--c5-permits);
    }
    .cta-card h4 { font-family: var(--narrow); font-size: 24px; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 8px; }
    .cta-card p { font-size: 15px; margin-bottom: 20px; }

    @media (max-width: 960px) {
      .row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 48px; }
      .guide-header { padding: 48px 0; }
      .big { font-size: clamp(48px, 10vw, 80px); }
    }
    .guide-next { padding: 48px 0; background: var(--ink); border-top: 2px solid rgba(255,255,255,.08); }
    .guide-next-label { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 10px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .1em; color: var(--yellow); margin-bottom: 16px; }
    .guide-next-links { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 20px; }
    .guide-next-links a { font-family: var(--narrow); font-size: 17px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--cream); text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid rgba(255,255,255,.2); padding-bottom: 2px; }
    .guide-next-links a:hover { color: var(--yellow); border-color: var(--yellow); }
  </style>

  <section class="guide-next">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="guide-next-label">Continue researching</p>
      <div class="guide-next-links">
        <a href="/cost/">What does a container cost?</a>
        <a href="/delivery/">How is it delivered?</a>
        <a href="/condition/">New vs. used condition grades</a>
        <a href="/shipping-containers-for-sale/">Browse container specs</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="guide-product-cta" style="padding: 64px 0; background: var(--ink); color: var(--cream);">
    <div class="wrap" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; gap: 24px; max-width: 680px;">
      <p class="m" style="color: var(--yellow); margin: 0;">Ready to move forward?</p>
      <h2 style="font-family: var(--narrow); font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 44px); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; margin: 0; line-height: 1.05;">Get your container quote</h2>
      <p style="font-size: 17px; opacity: .75; margin: 0; line-height: 1.5;">Tell us your size, condition, and delivery details and we'll get you an all-in number. Confirming permit and zoning requirements for your property is the buyer's responsibility.</p>
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <a href="/quote/" class="btn" style="background: var(--yellow); color: var(--ink); border-color: var(--yellow);">Start My Quote →</a>
        <a href="/shipping-containers-for-sale/" class="btn-ghost" style="color: var(--cream);">Browse containers</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
